 Nepalese nation has begun the daunting task of cremating the thousands of victims who were killed during Saturday 's earthquake .
With the death toll now standing at more than 4,000 , mass cremations have been taking place next to the Bagmati river , the waterway which divides the capital .
Today , plumes of white , acrid smoke could be seen floating across Kathmandu , as hundreds of bodies were burned in the ghats beside the river .